'Salient' may refer to:


* See Salients, re-entrants and pockets for the battlefield feature
* Salient (geography), part of a discrete territory projecting out of the main
  portion, bordered by foreign territory on three sides, into which it projects.
  These are also frequently called panhandles
* ''Salient'' (magazine), Victoria University of Wellington student publication
* Attitude (heraldry)#Salient
* 'Salient pole', a salient (i.e. projecting) electromagnetic pole of a
  field coil
